description: Along with the sister restaurant Viking Soul Food, The Wild Hunt is serving Portland a taste of delicious history with its authentic selection of Nordic tavern cuisine. Right in the lot of Teutonic Wines, you’ll find this stunning blue bus where a cool crew is preparing tasty and ornate Viking favorites. Their menu includes Seafood Chowder with saffron, cabbage, and potato, as well as a variety of Smørrebrød; open-faced sandwiches on sourdough rye with toppings like blood sausage, goat cheese, walnuts, and apples or Oregon pink shrimp, aioli, cherry tomatoes, and cucumbers. For this and much more, you must voyage out to The Wild Hunt!
name: The Wild Hunt
